</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">Sealed Air Corporation<br>2415&nbsp;Cascade Pointe Boulevard<br>Charlotte, North Carolina 28208</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:36pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">April&nbsp;5, 2018 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Dear Fellow Stockholder: </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">It is my pleasure to invite you to attend the Annual
Meeting of Stockholders of Sealed Air Corporation to be held on Thursday, May&nbsp;17, 2018, at 10:00 a.m., Eastern daylight time. We are pleased to announce that this year&#146;s Annual Meeting will be a &#147;virtual meeting.&#148; Each
stockholder will be able to participate in the Annual Meeting &#150; including casting votes and submitting questions &#150; by accessing a live webcast at <I>www.virtualshareholdermeeting.com/SEE2018</I> and entering the <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">16-digit</FONT> control number included on the stockholder&#146;s Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials or proxy card. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">During the Annual Meeting, stockholders will be asked to elect the entire Board of Directors, to amend and restate our 2014 Omnibus Incentive Plan, and to ratify the
appointment of Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as our independent auditor for 2018. We also will be asking stockholders for an approval, by an advisory vote, of our 2017 executive compensation as disclosed in the Proxy Statement for the Annual Meeting.
These matters are important, and we urge you to vote in favor of the election of each of the director nominees, the amendment and restatement of the 2014 Omnibus Incentive Plan, the ratification of the appointment of our independent auditor, and the
approval of our 2017 executive compensation. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We are again furnishing proxy materials to our stockholders over the Internet. This
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-proxy</FONT> process expedites stockholders&#146; receipt of proxy materials, lowers our costs and reduces the environmental impact of the Annual Meeting. Today we sent to most of our stockholders a Notice of
Internet Availability of Proxy Materials containing instructions on how to access our Proxy Statement for the Annual Meeting and our 2017 Annual Report to Stockholders, as well as how to vote via the Internet. Other stockholders will receive copies
of the Proxy Statement, a proxy card and the 2017 Annual Report by mail or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-mail.</FONT> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">It is important that you vote your
shares of common stock in person or by proxy, regardless of the number of shares you own. You will find the instructions for voting on your Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials or proxy card. We appreciate your prompt attention. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board of Directors invites you to participate in the Annual Meeting so that management can discuss business trends with you, listen to your suggestions and answer
your questions. Thank you for your continuing support, and we look forward to joining you at Sealed Air&#146;s first webcast stockholder meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Sincerely, </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g554645g58b00.jpg" ALT="LOGO">

Executive Officer </I></P>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g554645g35x57.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Notice of Annual Meeting of Stockholders </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Sealed Air Corporation, a Delaware corporation (&#147;Sealed Air&#148;), will hold its Annual Meeting of Stockholders (the &#147;Annual Meeting&#148;) on May&nbsp;17,
2018, at 10:00 a.m., Eastern daylight time. Each stockholder may participate in the Annual Meeting, including casting votes and submitting questions during the Annual Meeting, by accessing a live webcast at
<I>www.virtualshareholdermeeting.com/SEE2018</I> and then using the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">16-digit</FONT> control number provided on the Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials or proxy card being delivered to the stockholder.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The purposes for the Annual Meeting are to consider and vote upon: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Such other matters as properly come before the Annual Meeting </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board of Directors has fixed the close of business on
March&nbsp;19, 2018 as the record date for the determination of stockholders entitled to notice of, and to vote at, the Annual Meeting. Sealed Air is making available or mailing its 2017 Annual Report to Stockholders to all stockholders of record as
of the record date. Additional copies of the 2017 Annual Report are available upon written request to the Corporate Secretary at Sealed Air Corporation, 2415 Cascade Pointe Boulevard, Charlotte, North Carolina 28208. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Because it is important that as many stockholders as possible be represented at the Annual Meeting, stockholders should review the attached Proxy Statement promptly and
carefully and then vote. A stockholder may vote by following the instructions for voting set forth on the Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials or proxy card. A stockholder who receives a paper copy of the proxy card by mail will also
receive a postage-paid, addressed envelope that can be used to return the completed proxy card. A stockholder who joins the Annual Meeting may vote electronically at the Annual Meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Sealed Air will maintain a list of stockholders of record as of the record date at Sealed Air&#146;s corporate headquarters, 2415 Cascade Pointe Boulevard, Charlotte,
North Carolina, for a period of ten days prior to the Annual Meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On behalf of the Board of Directors, </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">T<SMALL>HOMAS</SMALL> C. L<SMALL>AGALY</SMALL> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Vice President, Acting General
Counsel and Secretary </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Charlotte, North Carolina </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">April&nbsp;5, 2018 </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B><I><A NAME="toc554645_1"></A>2018 Proxy Summary </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>This summary highlights information contained elsewhere in this Proxy Statement. This summary does not contain all of the information that you should consider, and
you should read the entire Proxy Statement carefully before voting. References in this Proxy Statement to &#147;Sealed Air,&#148; and to &#147;we,&#148; &#147;us,&#148; &#147;our&#148; and similar terms, refer to Sealed Air Corporation. </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Annual Meeting of Stockholders </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

independent auditor to examine and report on our consolidated financial statements and the effectiveness of our internal control over financial reporting for the fiscal year ending December&nbsp;31, 2018. </P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

<div style ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0px; MARGIN-RIGHT:0px;max-width:100%"><div style="width:97%; margin-top:1.5%; margin-left:1.5%; margin-right:-1.25%">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B><I>Key Features of Our Executive Compensation Program </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee believes that our executive compensation program follows best practices aligned to long-term stockholder interests, as summarized below: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="45%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="43%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" BGCOLOR="#12737c"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>What We Do</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c">&#10003;</FONT>&#8194;&#8201;Provide a majority
of compensation in performance-based compensation</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle">


<IMG SRC="g554645g86q58.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle">Consistent&nbsp;with&nbsp;our&nbsp;goal&nbsp;of&nbsp;creating a performance-oriented environment, 88% of total direct compensation for CEO, and 79% of total direct compensation for other named executive officers (excluding
Mr.&nbsp;Doheny), is performance-based</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#cefff4" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">
<P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c">&#10003;</FONT>&#8194;&#8201;Pay for performance based on goals for
both annual and long-term awards</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">


<IMG SRC="g554645g50n56.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">Use multiple, balanced measures, including use of both absolute and relative measures for long-term awards</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c">&#10003;</FONT>&#8194;&#8201;Balanced mix of
awards tied to annual and long-term performance</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle">


<IMG SRC="g554645g86q58.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle">For CEO, total direct compensation includes 16% in annual incentive award and 72% in long-term award at target; for 2017, 100% of long-term awards for named executive officers (other than Mr.&nbsp;Doheny) were
performance-based</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#cefff4" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">
<P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c">&#10003;</FONT>&#8194;&#8201;Stock ownership and retention
policy</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">


<IMG SRC="g554645g50n56.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">Multiple of base salary must be held in common stock &#151; 6x for CEO, 3.5x for CFO and 3x for other Senior Vice Presidents; 100% of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">after-tax</FONT> shares must be held until
ownership goal is met</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c">&#10003;</FONT>&#8194;&#8201;Compensation
recoupment (clawback) policy</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle">


<IMG SRC="g554645g86q58.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle">Recovery of annual or long-term incentive compensation based on achievement of financial results that were subsequently restated due to error or misconduct, regardless of whether named executive officer was responsible for the
error or misconduct</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#cefff4" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" BGCOLOR="#cefff4"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c">&#10003;</FONT>&#8194;&#8201;Receive advice from independent compensation consultant</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#cefff4" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">


<IMG SRC="g554645g50n56.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#cefff4" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">Compensation consultant (FW Cook) provides no other services to Sealed Air</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" BGCOLOR="#12737c"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>What We Don&#146;t Do</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c"><I>&times;</I></FONT>&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;No
supplemental executive retirement plans for named executive officers</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle">


<IMG SRC="g554645g86q58.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">Consistent with focus on performance-oriented environment; reasonable and competitive retirement programs offered</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#cefff4" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">
<P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c"><I>&times;</I></FONT>&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;No change in control
excise tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-ups</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">


<IMG SRC="g554645g50n56.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#cefff4">Consistent with focus on performance-oriented environment and commitment to best practices aligned to long-term stockholder interests</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c"><I>&times;</I></FONT>&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;No
excessive perquisites or severance benefits</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle">


<IMG SRC="g554645g86q58.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">Consistent with focus on performance-oriented environment and commitment to best practices aligned to long-term stockholder interests</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#cefff4" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" BGCOLOR="#cefff4"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c"><I>&times;</I></FONT>&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;No single-trigger vesting of equity compensation upon a change in control</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#cefff4" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>

<div style ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0px; MARGIN-RIGHT:0px;max-width:100%"><div style="width:97%; margin-top:1.5%; margin-left:1.5%; margin-right:-1.25%">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B><I>Key Elements of our Executive Compensation Program </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following table summarizes the main components of our executive compensation program for our named executive officers. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="33%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="3%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="31%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="30%"></TD></TR>


<TR BGCOLOR="#12737c" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Compensation Element</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Description</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Objectives</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">Base Salary</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Fixed cash compensation</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Appropriate level of fixed compensation based on role and
duties</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Assist with recruitment and retention</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#cefff4" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">Annual Incentive</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Annual cash award if performance metrics are achieved</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Target
award based on a percentage of base salary</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Payouts from <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">0-200%</FONT> of target based on company and individual performance</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Executive may elect all or a portion of award in form of restricted stock award
vesting over two years, with 25% enhancement</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Reward executives for driving superior operating and financial
results over a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-year</FONT> timeframe</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Create a direct connection between business success and financial
reward</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">Long-Term Incentives</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Performance share units earned based on performance, typically
over three-year period with <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">0-200%</FONT> payout</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Occasional awards of restricted stock or restricted stock units that vest at end
of three years of service</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Reward achievement of longer-term goals</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Create
direct connection between longer-term business success and financial reward</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Encourage retention</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#cefff4" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">Retirement Plans</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Standard plans generally offered to all salaried employees
based on location of services</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;No&nbsp;supplemental&nbsp;executive&nbsp;retirement plans</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Provide retirement income for participants</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Assist with
recruitment and retention</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">Deferred Compensation</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Elective, nonqualified deferred compensation plan for select
U.S. employees</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Permits deferral of salary and certain cash incentives</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;No Sealed
Air contributions are included</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Provide opportunity to save for retirement</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Assist with
recruitment and retention</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#cefff4" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">Post-Employment Benefits</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Executive Severance Plan provides competitive benefits in case
of involuntary termination; no single-trigger vesting of equity awards upon a change in control</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Mr.&nbsp;Peribere has post-employment benefits under the terms of his employment
arrangement</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#8194;&#8202;Mr.&nbsp;Doheny&nbsp;also&nbsp;has&nbsp;post-employment</FONT> benefits under the terms of his offer letter agreement</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Assure continuing performance of executives in face of
possible termination of employment without cause</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Assist with recruitment and retention</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Other Benefits</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Limited perquisites</P></TD>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B><I><A NAME="toc554645_2"></A>Questions and Answers about the Annual Meeting
</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:14pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>When and where will the Annual Meeting be held?</I> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B></B>This year the Annual Meeting of Stockholders of Sealed Air Corporation, which we refer to below as the Annual Meeting, will be held by webcast at <I>www.virtualshareholdermeeting.com/SEE2018</I>, beginning at
10:00 a.m., Eastern daylight time, on Thursday, May&nbsp;17, 2018. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>What materials have been prepared for stockholders in connection with the Annual Meeting?</I> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B></B>We are furnishing stockholders of record with the following proxy materials: </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">our 2017 Annual Report to Stockholders, which includes our audited consolidated financial statements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">this Proxy Statement for the 2018 Annual Meeting, which also includes a letter from our President and Chief Executive Officer to Stockholders and a Notice of Annual Meeting of Stockholders; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">for stockholders receiving printed copies of the 2017 Annual Report and Proxy Statement by mail, a proxy card for the Annual Meeting. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">These materials were first made available on the Internet or mailed to stockholders on or about April&nbsp;5, 2018. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>Why was I mailed a Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials rather than a printed set of proxy materials?</I> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B></B>In accordance with rules and regulations adopted by the Securities and Exchange Commission, we are furnishing the proxy materials to most stockholders by providing access via the Internet, instead of mailing
printed copies. This <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-proxy</FONT> process expedites our stockholders&#146; receipt of proxy materials, lowers our costs and reduces the environmental impact of the Annual Meeting. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials tells you how to access and review the proxy materials on the Internet and how to vote on the
Internet. The Notice also provides instructions you may follow to request paper or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-mailed</FONT> copies of our proxy materials. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B><I>Q:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I>Are the proxy materials available via the Internet?</I> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B></B>You can access the proxy materials for the Annual Meeting at <I>proxyreport.sealedair.com</I>. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B><I>Q:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I>What is a proxy?</I> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B></B>Because it is important that as many stockholders as possible be represented at the Annual Meeting, the Board of Directors is asking that you review the Proxy Statement carefully and then vote by following the
instructions set forth on the Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials or proxy card. In voting prior to the Annual Meeting, you will deliver your proxy to the Proxy Committee, which means you will authorize the Proxy Committee to vote
your shares at the Annual Meeting in the way you instruct. The Proxy Committee consists of Edward L. Doheny II, William G. Stiehl and Thomas C. Lagaly. All shares represented by valid proxies will be voted in accordance with the stockholder&#146;s
specific instructions. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right">7 </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>Who can vote at the Annual Meeting?</I> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B></B>Stockholders of record of our common stock at the close of business on March&nbsp;19, 2018, the record date, will be entitled to vote at the Annual Meeting. A total of 166,511,216 shares of common stock were
outstanding as of the record date. Each share outstanding on the record date will be entitled to one vote on each proposal. In addition, holders of record of W.R. Grace&nbsp;&amp; Co. common stock issued prior to March&nbsp;31, 1998 and outstanding
at the record date will have an aggregate of 1,698 votes on each proposal. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:4pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As a result, a total of 166,512,914 votes will be eligible
to be cast on each proposal at the Annual Meeting. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>What is a stockholder of record?</I> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B></B>A stockholder of record is a stockholder whose ownership of stock is reflected directly on the books and records of our transfer agent, Computershare. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>What does it mean for a broker or other nominee to hold shares in &#147;street name&#148;?</I> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B></B>If you beneficially own shares held in an account with a broker, bank or similar organization, that organization is the stockholder of record and is considered to hold those shares in &#147;street name.&#148;
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:4pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">An organization that holds your beneficially owned shares in street name will vote in accordance with the instructions you provide. If
you do not provide the organization with specific voting instructions with respect to a proposal, under the rules of the New York Stock Exchange the organization&#146;s authority to vote your shares will depend upon whether the proposal is
considered a &#147;routine&#148; or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-routine</FONT> matter. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The organization generally may vote your beneficially owned shares on routine items for which you have not provided voting instructions to the organization. The only routine matter expected to be voted on at the Annual
Meeting is the ratification of the appointment of our independent auditor for 2018 (Proposal&nbsp;3). </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The organization generally may not vote on <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-routine</FONT> matters, including Proposals 1, 2 and 4. Instead, it will inform the inspector of election that it does not have the
authority to vote on those matters. This is referred to as a &#147;broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-vote.&#148;</FONT> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:4pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For
the purpose of determining a quorum, we will treat as present at the Annual Meeting any proxies that are voted on any of the four proposals to be acted upon by the stockholders, including abstentions or proxies containing broker <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes.</FONT> </P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>How do I vote my shares if I do not attend the Annual Meeting?</I> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B></B><B><I>If you are a stockholder of record,</I></B> you may vote your shares of our common stock prior to the Annual Meeting as follows: </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I><U>Via the Internet</U></I>: You may vote via the Internet at <I>www.proxyvote.com</I>, in accordance with the voting instructions printed on the Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials and the proxy card.
Internet voting is available 24 hours a day until 11:59 p.m., Eastern daylight time, on May&nbsp;16, 2018. You will be given the opportunity to confirm that your instructions have been recorded properly. If you vote via the Internet, you do not need
to return a proxy card. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I><U>By Telephone</U></I>: If you receive a proxy card by mail, you may vote by calling
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">+1-800-690-6903</FONT></FONT></FONT> and following the instructions provided on the telephone line. Telephone voting is available 24&nbsp;hours a day
until 11:59 p.m., Eastern daylight time, on May&nbsp;16, 2018. <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Easy-to-follow</FONT></FONT> voice prompts allow you to vote your shares and confirm that your instructions have been
recorded properly. If you vote by telephone, you do not need to return a proxy card. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I><U>By Mail</U></I>: If you receive a proxy card by mail, you may vote by returning the completed and signed proxy card in the postage-paid return envelope provided with the proxy card. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">8 </P>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>What happens if I do not give specific voting instructions?</I> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

four proposals presented in this Proxy Statement and as the Proxy Committee may determine in its discretion on any other matters properly presented for a vote at the Annual Meeting. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If you are a beneficial owner of shares held in street name and do not provide specific voting instructions to the broker, bank or other organization
that is the stockholder of record of your shares, the organization generally may vote on routine matters but not on <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-routine</FONT> matters. The only routine matter expected to be voted on at the Annual Meeting is
the ratification of the appointment of our independent auditor for 2018 (Proposal 3). If the organization does not receive instructions from you on how to vote your shares on one or more of Proposals 1, 2 and 4, your shares will be subject to a
broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-vote</FONT> and no vote will be cast on those matters. See &#147;Q. What does it mean for a broker or other nominee to hold shares in &#145;street name&#146;?&#148; above. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>

<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">10 </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B><I><A NAME="toc554645_3"></A>Vote Required for Election or Approval
</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Introduction </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As of the
record date, which is the close of business on March&nbsp;19, 2018, 166,511,216 shares of common stock were outstanding, each of which is entitled to one vote at the Annual Meeting. In addition, holders of record of W.R. Grace &amp; Co. common stock
issued prior to March 31, 1998 and outstanding at the record date will have an aggregate of 1,698 votes on each proposal at the Annual Meeting, which means there will be a total of 166,512,914 votes eligible to be cast at the Annual Meeting. Holders
who are present in person or represented by proxy and who hold shares representing a majority of the votes eligible to be cast will constitute a quorum for the transaction of business at the Annual Meeting. For the purpose of determining a quorum,
we will treat as present at the Annual Meeting any proxies that are voted on any matter to be acted upon by the stockholders, as well as abstentions or any proxies containing broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes.</FONT> </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Proposal 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Election of Directors </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Each director will be elected by a vote of the majority of the votes cast with respect to that director, where a majority of the votes cast means that the number of
shares voted &#147;for&#148; a director must exceed the number of votes cast &#147;against&#148; the director. We will not count shares voted to &#147;abstain&#148; for the purpose of determining whether a director is elected. Similarly, broker <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> will not have any effect on the outcome of the election of directors since broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> are not counted as &#147;votes cast.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under our Certificate of Incorporation, our Bylaws and the Delaware General Corporation Law, a director holds office until a successor is elected and qualified or until
his or her earlier resignation or removal. Each of the nominees currently serves as one of our directors. If any of the nominees is not elected at the Annual Meeting, then the Bylaws provide that the director shall offer to resign from the Board of
Directors. The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee will make a recommendation to the Board whether to accept or reject the resignation, or whether other action should be taken. The Board will consider and act on the recommendation of the
Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee and publicly disclose its decision and the rationale behind it within ninety days from the date of the certification of the election results. The director who offers his or her resignation will not
participate in the decision of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee or the Board. If the Board accepts such resignation, then the Board may fill the vacancy resulting from that resignation or may reduce the number of directors that
constitutes the entire Board so that no vacancy exists. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Proposal 2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Amendment and Restatement of 2014 Omnibus
Incentive Plan </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The amendment and restatement of our 2014 Omnibus Incentive Plan must be affirmatively approved by a majority of the votes entitled to be
cast and present in person or represented by proxy at the Annual Meeting. Abstentions will count as votes against this proposal since shares with respect to which the stockholder abstains will be deemed present and entitled to vote. Broker <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> will have no effect on the outcome of this proposal since broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> are not counted as &#147;votes cast.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Proposal 3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ratification of Appointment of Independent Auditor for 2018 </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The ratification of Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as our independent auditor for the year ending December&nbsp;31, 2018 must be affirmatively approved by a majority of the
votes entitled to be cast and present in person or represented by proxy at the Annual Meeting. Abstentions will be deemed present and, therefore, will count as votes against this proposal. Because this proposal is considered a routine matter,
discretionary votes by brokers will be counted. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right">11 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Proposal 4. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Approval of 2017 Executive Compensation on an Advisory
Basis </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The advisory vote to approve our 2017 executive compensation must be affirmatively approved by a majority of the votes entitled to be cast and
present in person or represented by proxy at the Annual Meeting. Abstentions will count as votes against this proposal, since shares with respect to which the holder abstains will be deemed present and entitled to vote. Broker <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> will have no effect on the outcome of this proposal, since broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> are not counted as &#147;votes cast.&#148; </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">12 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B><I><A NAME="toc554645_4"></A>Corporate Governance </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc554645_5"></A>Corporate Governance Guidelines </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board of Directors has adopted and operates under Corporate Governance Guidelines that reflect our current governance practices in accordance with applicable
statutory and regulatory requirements, including those of the Securities and Exchange Commission, or SEC, and the New York Stock Exchange, or NYSE. The Corporate Governance Guidelines are available on our website at <I>www.sealedair.com.</I> </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc554645_6"></A>Independence of Directors </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under the Corporate Governance Guidelines and the requirements of the NYSE, the Board of Directors must consist of a majority of independent directors. The Board
annually reviews the independence of all <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors. The Board has established categorical standards consistent with the corporate governance standards of the NYSE to assist it in making
determinations of the independence of Board members. We have attached a copy of our Standards for Director Independence to this Proxy Statement as Annex A and also posted a copy on our website at <I>www.sealedair.com</I>. These categorical standards
require that, to be independent, a director may not have a material relationship with Sealed Air. Even if a director meets all categorical standards for independence, the Board reviews other relationships with Sealed Air in order to conclude that
each independent director has no material relationship with Sealed Air either directly or indirectly. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board has determined that the following director nominees
are independent: Michael Chu, Patrick Duff, Henry&nbsp;R. Keizer, Jacqueline&nbsp;B. Kosecoff, Neil Lustig, Richard&nbsp;L. Wambold and Jerry&nbsp;R. Whitaker. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc554645_7"></A>Code of Conduct </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We have a Code of Conduct applicable to all directors, officers and employees of Sealed
Air and its subsidiaries. We also have a supplemental Code of Ethics for Senior Financial Executives that applies to our Chief Executive Officer or CEO, Chief Financial Officer or CFO, Controller, Treasurer and all other employees performing similar
functions. We have posted the Code of Conduct and the Code of Ethics for Senior Financial Executives on our website at <I>www.sealedair.com</I>. We will post any amendments to the Code of Conduct and the Code of Ethics for Senior Financial
Executives on our website. In accordance with the requirements of the SEC and the NYSE, we will also post waivers applicable to any of our officers or directors from provisions of the Code of Conduct or the Code of Ethics for Senior Financial
Executives on our website. We have not granted any such waivers to date. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc554645_8"></A>Board Oversight of Risk </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board of Directors is actively involved in oversight of risks that could affect Sealed Air. While the Audit Committee oversees our major financial risk exposures
and the steps we have taken to monitor and control such exposures, and the Organization and Compensation Committee considers the potential of our executive compensation programs to raise material risks to Sealed Air, the Board as a whole is
responsible for oversight of our risk management processes and our enterprise risk management program. The Board regularly discusses risk management with management and among the directors during meetings. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc554645_9"></A>Communicating with Directors </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Stockholders and other interested parties may communicate directly with the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-management</FONT> directors of the Board of Directors
by writing to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Management</FONT> Directors, c/o Corporate Secretary, at Sealed Air Corporation, 2415&nbsp;Cascade Pointe Boulevard, Charlotte, North Carolina 28208, or by sending an email to
</P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right">13 </P>

</DIV></Center>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
<I>directors@sealedair.com</I>. In either case, the Chairman of the Board will be notified of all such correspondence as appropriate and will communicate with the other directors as appropriate
about the correspondence. We have posted information on how to communicate with the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-management</FONT> directors on our website at <I>www.sealedair.com</I>. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc554645_10"></A>Board Leadership Structure </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">William J. Marino, who is not standing for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election</FONT> at the Annual Meeting, was elected as the Chairman of the Board of
Directors in May 2014 and will continue in that role through the Annual Meeting. The Chairman presides at meetings of the Board at which he or she is present and leads the Board in fulfilling its responsibilities as specified in the Bylaws. The
Chairman has the right to call special and emergency meetings. The Chairman serves as the liaison for interested parties who request direct communications with the Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Notwithstanding the appointment of a Chairman, the Board considers all of its members responsible and accountable for oversight and guidance of its activities. All
directors have the opportunity to request items to be included on the agendas of upcoming meetings. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes having an independent chair is beneficial in
that it ensures that management is subject to independent and objective oversight and the independent directors have an active voice in the governance of Sealed Air. The leadership structure is reviewed annually as part of the Board&#146;s
self-assessment process, and changes may be made in the future to reflect the Board&#146;s composition as well as our needs and circumstances. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc554645_11"></A>Board of Directors Overview </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under our Bylaws and the Delaware General Corporation Law, our business and affairs are managed by or under the direction of the Board of Directors, which delegates
some of its responsibilities to its Committees. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board generally holds five regular meetings per year and meets on other occasions when circumstances require.
Directors spend additional time preparing for Board and Committee meetings, and we may call upon directors for advice between meetings. We encourage our directors to attend director education programs. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Corporate Governance Guidelines adopted by the Board provide that the Board will meet regularly in executive session without management in attendance. The Chairman
of the Board presides at each executive session. The Chairman&#146;s designee or the chair of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee serves as the presiding director if the Chairman of the Board is unable to serve. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under the Corporate Governance Guidelines, we expect directors to regularly attend meetings of the Board and of all Committees on which they serve and to review the
materials sent to them in advance of those meetings. We expect nominees for election at each Annual Meeting of stockholders to attend the Annual Meeting. Each of the eight nominees for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election</FONT> at the
Annual Meeting attended the 2017 Annual Meeting of Stockholders. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">During 2017 the Board held twelve meetings, excluding actions by unanimous written consent, and
held five executive sessions and five executive sessions with only independent directors. Each current director participated in at least 80&nbsp;percent of the aggregate number of meetings of the Board during 2017. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board maintains an Audit Committee, a Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee, and an Organization and Compensation Committee. The members of these Committees
consist only of </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">14 </P>

</DIV></Center>

the Audit Committee is independent, as defined in the listing standards of the NYSE, is financially literate, and is an audit committee financial expert in accordance with the standards of the SEC. The Audit Committee held sixteen meetings in 2017,

occasions, met privately with our management on seven occasions, and held four executive sessions with only <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors in attendance. Each member participated in at least 75% of the aggregate
number of meetings of the Audit Committee during 2017. No director is eligible to serve on the Audit Committee if that director simultaneously serves on the audit committees of three or more other public companies. </P>

William&nbsp;J.&nbsp;Marino, who serves ex officio. Mr.&nbsp;Marino is not standing for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election</FONT> at the Annual Meeting. The Board has determined that
each current member of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee is independent, as defined in the listing standards of the NYSE. The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee held five meetings in 2017, excluding actions by unanimous
written consent. During 2017, the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee held four executive sessions with only <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors in attendance. Each member participated in all of the meetings of
the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee during 2017. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee has the sole authority to retain, oversee and
terminate any consulting or search firm to be used to identify director candidates or assist in evaluating director compensation and to approve any such firm&#146;s fees and retention terms. Since 2010 the Nominating and Corporate Governance
Committee has engaged Frederic W. Cook&nbsp;&amp; Co., Inc., or FW&nbsp;Cook, to advise the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee on director compensation. FW&nbsp;Cook also advises the Organization and Compensation Committee regarding
executive compensation. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee will consider director nominees recommended by our stockholders in accordance with our
Policy and Procedure for Stockholder Nominations to the Board adopted by the Committee and approved by the Board, a copy of which is attached to this Proxy Statement as Annex B and posted on our website at <I>www.sealedair.com</I>. Recommendations
should be submitted to our Corporate Secretary in writing at Sealed Air Corporation, 2415&nbsp;Cascade Pointe Boulevard, Charlotte, North Carolina 28208, along with additional required information about the nominee and the stockholder making the
recommendation. Information on qualifications for nominations to the Board and procedures for stockholder nominations to the Board is included below under &#147;Proposal 1. Election of Directors&#151;Director Qualifications&#148; and
&#147;&#151;Identifying and Evaluating Nominees for Directors.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc554645_14"></A>Organization and Compensation Committee
</I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The principal responsibilities of the Organization and Compensation Committee, which we refer to as the Compensation Committee, are to assist the Board
of Directors in fulfilling its responsibilities relating to: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
